2005-08-27  Jim Hayward <jimhayward@linuxexperience.net>

	* src/: bf_lib.c, highlight.c, snr2.c: Backport a bug fix from CVS
	  HEAD in the pcre matching and converting byte offsets to
	  character offsets:

     In order process UTF-8 strings, you must build PCRE to
     include UTF-8 support in the code, and, in addition, you must
     call pcre_compile() with the PCRE_UTF8 option flag. When you do
     this, both the pattern and any subject strings that are matched
     against it are treated as UTF-8 strings instead of just
     strings of bytes.

